      "Description": "AI tools are increasingly being used to speed up contract review, but they come with important limitations that legal and business professionals need to understand. This lesson explores the types of nuanced legal risks that AI commonly overlooks, such as ambiguous clauses, implied obligations, and context-dependent language. You will learn why AI struggles to interpret commercial intent, industry-specific norms, and the broader relationship between contracting parties. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer picture of where AI can support your review process and where human judgement remains essential. No prior technical knowledge is required, making this lesson suitable for anyone involved in drafting, reviewing, or negotiating contracts.",
